parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Paint Chipping and Rusting on Windshield
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Paint chipping and rusting on the windshield can lead to reduced visibility, compromised structural integrity, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Paint chipping above the upper crease of the windshield
rusting present
reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The AEB system's faulty behavior can cause sudden, unnecessary braking, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The vehicle brakes unexpectedly when there is no obstacle in front
often when a vehicle in the adjacent lane stops.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The VDC system's failure to function properly can lead to loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: VDC system warnings appear on the dashboard
indicating a malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defects can lead to a decrease in the vehicle's overall appearance and potentially cause safety issues if the damaged components compromise structural integrity.
symptoms: Blistering on mirrors
front grille
side windows
Nissan emblem
and black trim; holes in the bottom of the vehicle; burning smell while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Impact Sensor and Front Distance Sensor Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sensors can compromise the vehicle's safety features, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Flashing front impact sensor and front distance sensor lights on the dashboard
often during early morning or late-night driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty blind spot warning system can increase the risk of accidents by failing to alert the driver of vehicles in the blind spot.
symptoms: Blind spot warning system fails to function
requiring a restart to reactivate; delayed acceleration after filling gas or stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, stranding the driver and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle will not shift gears
unable to accelerate beyond 35 MPH.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Forward Collision Warning and Vehicle Shutdown
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the forward collision warning system can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake or shut down, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities. This can also lead to a loss of control, especially on highways, and may cause other vehicles to crash into the affected vehicle.
symptoms: The forward collision warning system activates without any apparent reason
the vehicle suddenly brakes or slows down without warning
the vehicle shuts down
and multiple warning lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: VDC System Malfunction and False Accident Warnings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the VDC (Vehicle Dynamic Control) system can cause false warnings of accidents, which can be distracting and alarming for the driver, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The VDC warning light comes on without any apparent reason
the system reports a collision or accident when none has occurred
and the camera system may be faulty.
